quran[47]{c,v,t}:
  26,181,"Fill up the measure, and be not cheaters"
  26,182,and weigh with the straight balance
  26,183,"and diminish not the goods of the people, and do not mischief in the earth, working corruption"
  26,184,"Fear Him who created you, and the generations of the ancients"
  26,185,"They said, 'Thou art merely one of those that are bewitched"
  26,186,"thou art naught but a mortal, like us; indeed, we think that thou art one of the liars"
  26,187,"Then drop down on us lumps from heaven, if thou art one of the truthful"
  26,188,"He said, 'My Lord knows very well what you are doing"
  26,189,But they cried him lies; then there seized them the chastisement of the Day of Shadow; assuredly it was the chastisement of a dreadful day
  26,190,"Surely in that is a sign, yet most of them are not believers"
  26,191,"Surely thy Lord, He is the All-mighty, the All-compassionate"
  26,192,Truly it is the revelation of the Lord of all Being
  26,193,brought down by the Faithful Spirit
  26,194,"upon thy heart, that thou mayest be one of the warners"
  26,195,"in a clear, Arabic tongue"
  26,196,Truly it is in the Scriptures of the ancients
  26,197,"Was it not a sign for them, that it is known to the learned of the Children of Israel"
  26,198,If We had sent it down on a barbarian
  26,199,"and he had recited it to them, they would not have believed in it"
  26,200,Even so We have caused it to enter into the hearts of the sinners
  26,201,"who will not believe in it, until they see the painful chastisement"
  26,202,"so that it will come upon them suddenly, while they are not aware"
  26,203,"and they will say, 'Shall we be respited"
  26,204,"What, do they seek to hasten Our chastisement"
  26,205,What thinkest thou? If We give them enjoyment of days for many years
  26,206,then there comes on them that they were promised
  26,207,"what will it then avail them, the enjoyment of days they were given"
  26,208,"Never a city We destroyed, but it had warners"
  26,209,for a reminder; and never did We wrong
  26,210,Not by the Satans has it been brought down
  26,211,"it behoves them not, neither are they able"
  26,212,"Truly, they are expelled from hearing"
  26,213,"So call thou not upon another god with God, lest thou shouldst be one of those that are chastised"
  26,214,"And warn thy clan, thy nearest kin"
  26,215,"Lower thy wing to those who follow thee, being believers"
  26,216,"then, if they disobey thee, say, 'I am quit of that you do"
  26,217,"Put thy trust in the All-mighty, the All-compassionate"
  26,218,who sees thee when thou standest
  26,219,and when thou turnest about among those who bow
  26,220,"Surely He is the All-hearing, the All-knowing"
  26,221,Shall I tell you on whom the Satans come down
  26,222,They come down on every guilty impostor
  26,223,"They give ear, but most of them are liars"
  26,224,And the poets -- the perverse follow them
  26,225,hast thou not seen how they wander in every valley
  26,226,and how they say that which they do not
  26,227,"Save those that believe, and do righteous deeds, and remember God oft, and help themselves after being wronged; and those who do wrong shall surely know by what overturning they will he overturned"